1 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
2 direct the Louisiana State Board of Medical Examiners to conduct, or cause to be conducted,
3 a two-year study of the feasibility and advisability of establishing a physician review panel
4 process for certain complaints against physicians prior to escalation to formal disciplinary
5 proceedings.
6 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study shall examine all of the following
7 issues:
8 (1) Whether complaints involving clinical decision making, diagnosis, treatment,
9 prescribing, supervision of clinical care, documentation of care, or standard of care should
10 be eligible for physician review panel consideration, and whether complaints primarily
11 involving billing disputes, fee disputes, other financial complaints, or allegations of sexual
12 misconduct should be excluded.
13 (2) Whether physician review panel consideration should be mandatory or optional
14 at the election of the physician who is the subject of the complaint.
15 (3) Whether the time limitation provided in R.S. 37:1285.2(A)(2) should be tolled
16 during physician review panel consideration.
17 (4) Appropriate qualifications for panel members, including active clinical practice
18 requirements, board certification in a specialty recognized by the American Board of
19 Medical Specialties when reasonably available, use of physicians in the same specialty or
20 a substantially similar field of practice, and use of non-board-certified physicians when
21 board certification is unavailable and the physician has substantial experience in the area of
22 practice under review.
23 (5) Appropriate procedures for empaneling physician review panels, including
24 deadlines for designation of members, methods of resolving deadlocks in the selection of a
25 third member, and procedures for filling vacancies or resolving recusals and
26 disqualifications.
27 (6) The proper role and legal effect of a physician review panel recommendation,
28 including whether such a recommendation should be advisory only or entitled to greater
29 weight in the disciplinary process.
