1 (7) Appropriate confidentiality protections for records, notes, data, studies, analyses,
2 exhibits, written recommendations, findings, determinations, and proceedings of the
3 physician review panel, including whether protections similar to those found in R.S.
4 13:3715.3 should apply.
5 (8) Appropriate compensation for panel members and the advisability of imposing
6 a fee on a physician who elects physician review panel consideration, including whether any
7 such fee should be capped.
8 (9) The effect such a process would have on administrative efficiency, physician
9 participation, due process, protection of the public, and the timely resolution of complaints.
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that, in conducting the study, the LSBME shall
11 consult with representatives of the Louisiana State Medical Society, physicians from a
12 variety of specialties, and such other stakeholders as the board deems appropriate.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the LSBME shall submit an initial progress
14 report on the study not later than December 1, 2027, and shall submit a final written report
15 of its findings, conclusions, and recommendations not later than February 1, 2028, to the
16 House Committee on Health and Welfare and the Senate Committee on Health and Welfare.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
18 executive director of the Louisiana State Board of Medical Examiners and to the president
19 of the Louisiana State Medical Society.
